article.headline: New Hampshire 75, Albany 72 (OT)
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Blagoj Janev made four free throws in the last 30 seconds of overtime as New Hampshire beat Albany 75-72 Sunday in America East Conference play. Janev had 24 points for New Hampshire. Albany (10-8, AE 5-2) led briefly in overtime on Jamar Wilson's three-pointer before the visitors (7-12, AE 4-4) took over. Levi Levine tipped in a missed jumper for Albany to send the game into overtime. Janev's three-point attempt failed as time ran out. Albany trailed by two at the half before taking a 49-43 lead on a 7-0 run. Wilson led Albany with 21 points. New Hampshire has won five of its last six games.
